    "chemicalDescription": [
      "r-(Oligopeptide-133 sh-Oligopeptide-1) is a single chain fusion peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the genes encoding for Oligopeptide-133 and sh-Oligopeptide-1. The fusion peptide contains 79 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
